    {
      "id": "UgyZ2XpJ1l0Glgo6ms14AaABAg",
      "author": "@massimoisabelle6391",
      "authorImage": "https://yt3.ggpht.com/ytc/AIdro_kMZSJq7jrV3x6iOEgva7hNG-e_A0VLjbGdLyCrGcKI=s48-c-k-c0x00ffffff-no-rj",
      "text": "The United States is truly a country that deserves to be explored from coast to coast. I’ve had the opportunity to visit New York State and, of course, New York City, and during the same trip I also spent time in Montana. Both places left a lasting impression on me, but Montana was especially memorable.\n\nThe natural beauty there is simply breathtaking, with stunning lakes set against mountain backdrops, such as Lake McDonald, Avalanche Lake, and Kootenai Falls Swinging Bridge. I also loved visiting the National Bison Range near Polson. The scenery, wildlife, and sense of space made it one of the highlights of my travels in the U.S.\n\nThat’s why I was a little surprised not to see Montana included in your list of 14 destinations. Perhaps it deserves an honorable mention—or even a spot on an expanded list of 15! After all, Glacier National Park is often recognized as one of the very best national parks in the United States, and for me it certainly lived up to that reputation.\n\nThank you for sharing such a great list and inspiring more travel ideas!",
